commits.author: Uwe Schindler
commits.sourceNew:
/** Lower-level search API. * *

{@link Collector#collect(int)} is called for every matching document. * *

Applications should only use this if they need all of the * matching documents. The high-level search API ({@link * Searcher#search(Query, int)}) is usually more efficient, as it skips * non-high-scoring hits. *

Note: The score passed to this method is a raw score. * In other words, the score will not necessarily be a float whose value is * between 0 and 1. * @throws BooleanQuery.TooManyClauses */ public void search(Query query, Collector results) throws IOException { search(createWeight(query), null, results); }
